  CLEAN DECOMPOSITION:
  k-cycle = (v₁,v₂,...,v_k) as cycle.
  Consider v₁ and v₃.

  If v₁→v₃ (Case A): (v₁,v₂,v₃) is transitive.
    k-cycle ≡ (v₁,v₃)+(v₃,v₄)+...+(v_k,v₁) mod B₁   [a (k-1)-cycle]
    Induction reduces this to 3-cycles.

  If v₃→v₁ (Case B): (v₁,v₂,v₃) is a 3-cycle.
